@*
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    BnThemedPanel — BnDemo's cascading consumer (Phase 3.4): reads the
    cascaded BnTheme and renders a BnView with the theme's current
    background — the "themed child" whose re-render on theme change is
    DoD #6's proof surface. Phase 7.1 Gate 2: authored in .razor, parity
    proven inside BnDemo's golden-vs-twin (the panel renders twice in the
    demo tree — the form div and the echo panel — so every one of its
    patches was under the byte-identical comparison).

    VISIBILITY CHANGE, FORCED AND RECORDED (7.1 Gate 2): the hand-written
    panel was `internal`, declared inside BnDemo.cs. The Razor compiler's
    component discovery only considers PUBLIC types — an internal component
    in markup silently parses as a plain HTML element (an unknown-element
    wire violation the twin test would catch loudly) — and the generated
    class is `public partial` with no way to narrow it. So converting
    BnDemo to .razor REQUIRED the panel to go public; given that, authoring
    the panel itself in .razor is the cleaner half of the same decision.
    Pre-1.0 surface addition, recorded for the phase conclusion.
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*@
<BnView BackgroundColor="@(Theme?.Background)" Padding="@Padding" ChildContent="@ChildContent" />

@code {
    /// <summary>The cascaded theme (see BnTheme: a NEW record instance per
    /// toggle is what makes CascadingValue notify its consumers).</summary>
    [CascadingParameter] public BnTheme? Theme { get; set; }

    /// <inheritdoc cref="BnView.Padding"/>
    [Parameter] public float? Padding { get; set; }

    /// <summary>Nested content rendered inside the themed view.</summary>
    [Parameter] public RenderFragment? ChildContent { get; set; }
}
